## YAML-lite value ADT

```scalascript
// A scalar string value.
case class YStr(v: String)

// A mapping (ordered sequence of key-value pairs).
case class YMap(pairs: List[Any])

// A sequence (list of values).
case class YSeq(items: List[Any])
```

## Key and scalar parsers

```scalascript
// Horizontal whitespace.
val hspace: Parser[Any] = Parser.regex("[ \t]*")

// A YAML key: identifier or quoted string, followed by a colon.
val yamlKey: Parser[Any] =
  (identifier <~ hspace <~ Parser.char(':'))
    .named("yaml key")

// A scalar value: everything to end-of-line, trimmed.
val scalarValue: Parser[Any] =
  Parser.regex("[^\n]+").map(s => YStr(s.asInstanceOf[String].trim))

// Optional trailing space + newline after a scalar.
val eol: Parser[Any] = hspace <~ Parser.char('\n')

// Blank lines.
val blankLines: Parser[Any] = Parser.regex("([ \t]*\n)*")
```

## Value parser (forward reference for recursion)

```scalascript
// Forward reference — filled in below after yamlMapping is defined.
var yamlValueRef: Parser[Any] = Parser.fail("yamlValueRef not initialized")

// A sequence item starts with "- " then a value.
val seqItem: Parser[Any] =
  (Parser.string("- ") ~> yamlValueRef)

// A sequence block: one or more "- value" items at the same indent.
val yamlSeq: Parser[Any] =
  seqItem.block.map(items => YSeq(items.asInstanceOf[List[Any]]))

// A mapping: one or more key-value pairs at the same indent level.
// Each pair is:  key: <scalar>   (inline)
//             or key:\n  <nested mapping or sequence>  (block)
val yamlPair: Parser[Any] =
  Parser.readCtx { ctx =>
    val level = ctx match
      case ic: IndentContext => ic.currentLevel
      case _                 => 1
    // Try block value first (no inline scalar after the colon).
    val blockValue: Parser[Any] =
      (Parser.char('\n') ~> blankLines ~> yamlValueRef.block.withIndent(level + 2))
        .map(v => YMap(v.asInstanceOf[List[Any]]))
    // Inline scalar: space + text on same line.
    val inlineValue: Parser[Any] =
      (hspace ~> scalarValue <~ eol)
    (yamlKey ~ (blockValue | inlineValue))
      .map(pair => (pair._1, pair._2))
  }

val yamlMapping: Parser[Any] =
  yamlPair.block.map(pairs => YMap(pairs.asInstanceOf[List[Any]]))

// Initialize the forward reference.
yamlValueRef = yamlMapping | yamlSeq | scalarValue
```

## Top-level document

```scalascript
// A YAML-lite document is a mapping at column 1.
val yamlDoc: Parser[Any] =
  (blankLines ~> yamlMapping <~ blankLines)
```

## Pretty-printer

```scalascript
def renderYaml(v: Any, indentLevel: Int): String =
  val pad = "  " * indentLevel
  v match
    case YStr(s)    => s
    case YSeq(items) =>
      items.asInstanceOf[List[Any]].map(i => pad + "- " + renderYaml(i, indentLevel)).mkString("\n")
    case YMap(pairs) =>
      pairs.asInstanceOf[List[Any]].map { p =>
        val (k, value) = p.asInstanceOf[(Any, Any)]
        value match
          case YMap(_) | YSeq(_) =>
            pad + k + ":\n" + renderYaml(value, indentLevel + 1)
          case _ =>
            pad + k + ": " + renderYaml(value, indentLevel)
      }.mkString("\n")
    case _ => v.toString
```

## Sample document

```scalascript
val sample = """server:
  host: localhost
  port: 8080
  tls:
    cert: /etc/tls/cert.pem
    key: /etc/tls/key.pem

database:
  host: db.internal
  port: 5432
  name: myapp
  pool:
    min: 2
    max: 10
"""
```

## Parse and render

```scalascript
yamlDoc.parseLayoutWith(sample.trim, IndentContext.at(1)) match
  case ParseOk(doc, _, _) =>
    println("Parsed successfully.")
    println(renderYaml(doc, 0))
  case ParseErr(e) =>
    println("Parse error at offset " + e.pos.offset + ": " + e.message)
```

## Query helpers

```scalascript
// Look up a key in a YMap, returning its value or None.
def yGet(doc: Any, key: String): Option[Any] =
  doc match
    case YMap(pairs) =>
      pairs.asInstanceOf[List[(Any, Any)]].find(_._1 == key).map(_._2)
    case _ => None

// Extract a scalar string value.
def yStr(doc: Any, key: String): Option[String] =
  yGet(doc, key).flatMap {
    case YStr(s) => Some(s)
    case _       => None
  }
```

## Demo queries

```scalascript
yamlDoc.parseLayoutWith(sample.trim, IndentContext.at(1)) match
  case ParseOk(doc, _, _) =>
    val serverHost = yGet(doc, "server").flatMap(s => yStr(s, "host"))
    val dbName     = yGet(doc, "database").flatMap(d => yStr(d, "name"))
    val poolMax    = yGet(doc, "database")
                       .flatMap(d => yGet(d, "pool"))
                       .flatMap(p => yStr(p, "max"))
    println("server.host = " + serverHost.getOrElse("?"))
    println("database.name = " + dbName.getOrElse("?"))
    println("database.pool.max = " + poolMax.getOrElse("?"))
  case ParseErr(e) =>
    println("error: " + e.message)
```
